title: The Toledo Museum of Art - European Paintings (Art Ebook).pdf
description:
396 pag / pdf / Pennsylvania State Univ / 1976 / English / ISBN-10: 0271012498 / 43 MB

This comprehensive, fully illustrated catalogue of The Toledo Museum's world-famous European paintings presents full scholarly documentation of 444 works of art. Recognized internationally for its carefully selected masterpieces, Toledo's Museum includes among its European paintings works by leading painters of all periods, including Rubens, Rembrandt, Poussin, Watteau, Boucher, Fragonard, El Greco, Manet, Cezanne, Renoir, Van Gogh, and Picasso.The text section, arranged alphabetically, provides a separate entry for each painting, including a biography of each artist, provenance of each painting, current bibliography and critical discussions of scholarly regences, attributions, and iconography.Because of the importance of the Museum's collection of European paintings and the comprehensive nature of this scholarly catalogue, this book will become an important reference for students and scholars of art history, as well as a source of visual pleasure to everyone.
